    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-23T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.05/531: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-23T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 23, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 23—7:39 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Legation’s 6, February 8, 10 a.m. The Italian Government replied February
                    20th expressing sympathy with Egyptian wishes but <pb facs="0676" n="574"
                        xml:id="pg_574"/> stating that presidency of Chambers will require
                    modification rather than interpretation of existing regulations. Use of the
                    Arabic language should be given practical solution which must not interfere with
                    normal functioning of courts or modify their organization or character.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
